One person has been confirmed dead with many others injured during the Yoruba Nation agitators rally in the Ojota area of Lagos , this morning. Though details of how the planned rally to press for self -determination assumed a violent twist could not be immediately ascertained. An unconfirmed report had it that three persons, including a policeman were gunned down in the cross fire. But the Lagos State Police Public Relations Officer, SP Benjamin Hudenyin said only one person lost his life, adding that policemen were in the area to ensure calm.